Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Library Technician (Internal-External) Sudbury , ON Description Position SummaryCambrian College’s Library and Learning Commons requires a Library Technician beginning June 2023. (This role may require some evening and weekends.)
Note: Internal candidates, as defined by the Full-Time Support Staff Collective Agreement, will be given first consideration.Duties and ResponsibilitiesAct as a primary point of contact for a diverse population of clients within the Cambrian Community, as well as alumni and prospective students, who access the library facilities, systems, and services.Provide high quality reference and research assistance, to local and distance users, in multiple modalities and settings using a wide range of resources in varying formats. This includes reference services in-person, by telephone, and online including email and virtual chat.Contribute to core Library functions such as access and technical services support, cataloguing, print and electronic resource acquisitions, material processing, interlibrary loan and document delivery functions, shelving and stacks maintenance and organization of Library materials using a variety of resources and tools.Maintain and update Library web pages and web resources; maintain and troubleshoot access to resources in all formats (print and electronic); update and maintain instructional/information resource pages using appropriate technologies and applications. This includes the creation of instructional materials in a variety of formats including print handouts, web-based research guides, and video tutorials on the use of library research tools.Support information literacy, copyright compliance, and e-learning by liaising with faculty regularly to discuss library collections and services, providing library orientations and assisting students with technical questions regarding accessing the library’s resources.Ensure effective promotion of the library with outreach and engagement activities.QualificationsRequired Completion of a two-year Library and Information Technician diploma or equivalent. (A copy of educational documents must be submitted with application *** education completed outside of Canada, applicants are required to submit a WES or ICAS with their application)One year of experience providing customer service in a busy library environment; a working knowledge of complex library software, resources and reference functions; an aptitude for technology.The ability to balance multiple tasks with frequent interruptions. Excellent research, technical, communication, and analytical skills.Excellent interpersonal skills and the ability to exercise tact and good judgment.Must demonstrate a strong capacity for public speaking in order to effectively deliver workshops and class presentations.Proficiency in Microsoft Office software (Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Outlook).Collaborative professional who promotes teamwork and works cohesively within a team-oriented environment. Additional Asset/Preferred Experience in a postsecondary educational setting.Required InformationTo be considered, candidates must provide the following as an attachment:Educational documentsWES/ICAS Equivalence if degrees/diplomas are from a Non-Canadian University Compensation $30.87 Hourly Closes: 25 May, 2023 Cambrian College of Applied Arts &amp; Technology Sudbury , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
