Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Training Librarian (FT) St Catharines , ON Description Posted: May 16, 2023 Closes: May 28, 2023, 5:00 pm Training Librarian (Full-Time) Permanent Location: Central Library Job Summary: This position reports to the Manager of Customer Service and is accountable for the development and delivery of training programs for staff and customers. Functioning in a team environment, the Training Librarian will provide and support staff and customer training modules and sessions. Identifying trends from working with staff and the public, providing information and reference services, reader’s advisory and digital assistance. They will ensure the strategic goals of St Catharines Public Library are met through customer service excellence and delivery of their portfolio assignments through training, coaching and supporting library staff. Duties and Responsibilities: For the Training Librarian Job Description, please see myscpl.ca/jobs. Qualifications: / Requirements: Master’s Degree in Library Science from an ALA accredited library school.Minimum 2 years’ experience in public library program and/or training planning and delivery.Demonstrate experience with technology instruction to support a wide variety of devices and platforms.Experience in project management and outcome measurement is an asset.Experience providing library advocacy is an asset.Driver’s license and access to a vehicle is required for outreach.A Police Record Check including Vulnerable Sector Screening is required and is a condition of employment. Hours of Work: Weekdays, evenings, and weekends as required, 35 hours per week. Hourly Rate: $31.319 - $36.946 per hour (Pay Group 12, January 2021 FT Schedule) plus $1.98 Pay Equity adjustment. All Union positions are currently under pay grid negotiations. How to Apply: Please submit your cover letter and current resume to hr@myscpl.ca . We thank all who apply. Only those selected for an interview will be contacted. St. Catharines Public Library is an equal opportunity employer committed to inclusive, barrier-free recruitment, selection processes, and work environments.COVID-19 vaccines are a requirement of the job unless you have an exemption on a medical or other protected ground pursuant to the Ontario Human Rights Code (OHRC). Please advise Human Resources to ensure your accommodation needs under the OHRC and Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act are provided through all stages of the recruitment process. Compensation $31.319 - $36.946 per hour (Pay Group 12, January 2021 FT schedule) plus $1.98 Pay Equity adjustment. All Union positions are currently under pay grid negotiations. Closes: 28 May, 2023 St. Catharines Public Library St Catharines , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
