Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Senior High Density Access and Retrieval Associate Toronto , ON Description Req ID: 30536 Faculty/Division: Library Department: Downsview Campus: St. George (Downtown Toronto) Description: About Us: The University of Toronto Libraries system is the largest academic library in Canada and is consistently ranked in the top ten among academic research libraries in North America. The system consists of 40 libraries located on three university campuses: St. George, Mississauga, and Scarborough. This array of college libraries, special collections, and specialized libraries and information centres supports the teaching and research requirements of over 300 graduate programs, more than 70 professional programs, and about 700 undergraduate degree programs. In addition to more than 15 million volumes in 341 languages, the library system currently provides access to millions of electronic resources in various forms and over 31,000 linear metres of archival material. More than 150,000 new print volumes are acquired each year. The Libraries' data centre houses more than 500 servers with a storage capacity of 1.5 petabytes. Your Opportunity: Working at the UTL at Downsview location and reporting to the Manager, Downsview, the Senior High Density Access and Retrieval Associate is responsible for coordinating the work of processing and fulfilling access to Downsview collections. Acts as a workflow leader to ensure that staff perform the required tasks. Acts as a liaison with other departments and staff of the library or the University required to complete the work of the unit. Contributes to metadata clean up projects as needed. Participates in preparing items for shelving, which have been transferred to UTL at Downsview, and retrieving and circulating these items, as requested. The range of duties includes: physical preparation of storage trays, barcoding items, shelving and retrieving with the use of a specialized fork-lift, processing requests, opening and closing the facility, shipping and receiving, providing information in response to inquiries from patrons, and participating in the quality assurance process. May be responsible for other duties such as record maintenance and digital scanning. Performs other related duties, as required. Required Qualifications: Formal Education: Some post-secondary education required; or an equivalent combination of education and experience. Certification on the specialized fork-lift used in this environment. Experience: A minimum of one year of related experience working in a research or academic library setting required. Working knowledge of library systems required. Requires knowledge of bibliographic database searching. Evidence of initiative, analytical ability, and flexibility to respond to workflow demands. Ability to work independently with minimum supervision, and to complete detailed work assignments promptly and accurately. Proven ability to work productively and efficiently in conformity with departmental standards and procedures. Ability to handle large volumes of library materials. Excellent communication and interpersonal skills. Skills: Facility to learn new systems and adapt to new technology and new workflows. Demonstrated commitment to the values of inclusivity, diversity, equity, and accessibility. Demonstrated strong organizational, analytical, and time management skills. Basic knowledge of windows software applications, web browsers, and basic knowledge of word processing and e-mail software required. Experience operating warehouse equipment desired. NOTE: This position is located at UTL at Downsview on Dufferin St. at Steeles Ave. This position is not eligible for a hybrid work arrangement. Closing Date: 05/22/2023,11:59PM ET Employee Group: CUPE 1230 Appointment Type: Budget - Continuing Schedule: Full-Time Pay Scale Group &amp; Hiring Zone: CUPE 1230 (4U) - Step 1: $65,477 - Step 2: $68,040 - Step 3: $70,724 Job Category: Library ServicesTo Apply, please visit https://jobs.utoronto.ca/job/Toronto-Senior-High-D... Compensation CUPE 1230 (4U) - Step 1: $65,477 - Step 2: $68,040 - Step 3: $70,724 Closes: 22 May, 2023 University of Toronto Libraries Toronto , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
