Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Librarian, Business Liaison and Copyright Kelowna , BC Description OKANAGAN COLLEGEOkanagan College transforms lives and communities. We are one of Canada's leading colleges. We create outstanding educational experiences for our learners, both students and employees. We work and learn in a welcoming and caring culture. We are a catalyst for change through collaboration with our learners and partners. We serve, lead and anticipate the social, economic and environmental needs of communities.Position Title:Librarian, Business Liaison and CopyrightCompetition Number:C002381Division/Portfolio:Library ServicesDepartment/Program:LibraryCampus/Centre:KelownaYour Opportunity:Under the general direction of the Director of Library Services, is responsible for liaison with the Business Administration department and one or more other instructional departments; coordinates Interlibrary Loan and Reference Services at the Kelowna Campus; works with the Director of Library Services/Copyright Officer to oversee activities related to copyright compliance and education. Supervises the Library Technician, Reference, Interlibrary Loan and Copyright. Other duties include reference, library research instruction, collection development, professional development, service, and may include scholarly activity.Education and Experience:Required:A degree from an accredited master’s program in Library and Information Studies.Desirable:Recent experience in an academic library, including experience in the provision of library instruction and reference servicesExperience assisting library users with both print and electronic resources, including creating instructional materials in a variety of formatsExperience working with interlibrary loan and/or copyright in a library settingFunctions and Duties:1. Acts as liaison to the Business Administration department and other instructional departments as appropriate to ensure that library collections and services meet the needs of students and instructional employees2. Works closely with the Kelowna Campus Librarian to deliver library public services on the Kelowna campus and to represent the Library on Kelowna campus committees3. In conjunction with the Library Technician, Reference, Interlibrary Loan and Copyright and other Kelowna Public Services Library Technicians, coordinates system-wide Interlibrary Loan services4. Coordinates reference services at the Kelowna Campus Library, including training reference assistants and new librarians on reference procedures and best practices, and coordination of the reference schedule in conjunction with the Library Technician, Reference, Interlibrary Loan and Copyright for both in-person help at the Research Desk and online research help via email5. Supervises the Library Technician, Reference, Interlibrary Loan and Copyright6. Develops and delivers copyright-related education and training to students and employees7. Works with the Library Technician, Reference, Interlibrary Loan and Copyright to manage digitization requests for the Library’s digital resource management system and copyright permission requests8. Makes recommendations to the Copyright Officer on issues related to copyright management and compliance9. Actively integrates Equity, Diversity, Inclusion and Social Justice principles into all areas of practice related to the responsibilities of the position.10. Provides reference services, in person, by email, and in a real-time virtual environment11. Prepares and delivers in-class instruction to students, in conjunction with the Kelowna campus librarian and other librarians12. Prepares guides and tutorials on the use of Library collections and services, using a variety of media and formats13. Participates in the development of the Library collection by working with the Collections and Metadata Librarian and departmental Library representatives to plan for resource needs and to select books, media and other materials14. Contributes to planning and development of Library policies and procedures by participating in the Library Management Committee15. Engages in professional development activity intended to promote subject area and technical competence in librarianship and information science16. Engages in service activities that support the College and/or the profession and/or the community17. If requested and approved, may engage in scholarly activity, which may include scholarship, research and creative activity18. Other related librarian duties.Skills and Abilities:Familiar with, and supportive of, new and emerging technologies in library servicesStrong oral and written communication skillsAbility to promote contact and communication among students and facultyAbility to work independently, and as part of a team, to assist in the delivery of library servicesAbility to work with people of diverse educational and socio-cultural backgroundsStrong organizational skills in managing multiple activities and working under time constraintsDemonstrated ability to learn new skillsDemonstrated ability to teach in a variety of situations, across a diversity of subjects and program levels, and using a variety of methods, including active learningSome evening and weekend work may be required.Appointment Type:Faculty - Full-time ContinuingAppointment Start Date:08/08/2023Schedule:35 hours per week, Monday through FridaySome evening and weekend work may be required from time to time.Annual Salary/Hourly Rate:Salary range $62,828 to $100,958 with normal starting salary between $69,017 and $75,206 annually*, dependent on relevant education and experience. *Note: Part-time Term and summer appointments subject to adjustment factors as per Collective Agreement.Posting Opening Date:04/24/2023Posting Closing Date:05/22/2023APPLICATIONS:To apply for this position, please go to our employment site: https://www.employmentopportunities.okanagan.bc.ca and complete an on-line application. All applications must be submitted through our employment site to be considered.Okanagan College is committed to increasing the equitable and inclusive participation of marginalized people in all aspects of college life. We welcome and encourage applications from Indigenous Peoples, Black People, members of racialized groups/visible minorities, people with disabilities and people with diverse gender identities or expressions. People with disabilities who anticipate needing accommodations for any part of the application process may contact, in confidence, AccessibilityHR@okanagan.bc.ca Compensation Salary range $62,828 to $100,958 with normal starting salary between $69,017 and $75,206 annually*, dependent on relevant education and experience. *Note: Part-time Term and summer appointments subject to adjustment factors as per Collective Agreement. Closes: 22 May, 2023 Okanagan College Kelowna , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
